name: 02-Data Preparation
content:
Data Description:-

These Datasets are designed to provide information that will help predict excess usage of water in various industries :-


  • Date: The date of the record (string format).
  • Employee_Count: The number of employees recorded on the specified date (integer).
  • Main Pipe Length: The length of the main pipe, likely in meters or kilometers (integer).
  • Daily Abstraction Avg: The average amount of water abstracted daily (floating-point).
  • Cooling Water: The volume of water used for cooling (integer).
  • Injection Water: The volume of water used for injection (integer).
  • Production Water: The volume of water used for production (integer).
  • Processing Water: The volume of water used for processing (integer).
  • Waste Water: The volume of wastewater recorded (integer).
  • Over Abstraction: Instances or volume of water abstracted beyond the norm (integer).
  • Leakage: The amount of water lost due to leaks (integer).
  • Over_Demand: Instances of demand exceeding supply or capacity (integer).
  • Unique_Reasons: The count of unique reasons leading to issues or anomalies (integer).
  • Large_Industry: Indicates involvement or volume of large industries (integer, likely a count).
  • Mid_Industry: Indicates involvement or volume of medium industries (integer, likely a count).
  • Small_Industry: Indicates involvement or volume of small industries (integer, likely a count).
  • Date_dt: The formatted date in a standardized datetime format (string).
  • Date_dt_month: The month extracted from the date (integer).
  • Date_dt_dayofweek: The day of the week extracted from the date (integer, 0 = Monday).
  • Date_dt_monthname: The name of the month extracted from the date (string).
  • Over_Abstraction_Median: Median value for over abstraction, possibly used as a threshold (integer).
  • Excess_Usage: Binary or categorical indicator for excessive water usage (integer or string).


Data Integration:-

  • Aggregate Features: Create new features by combining related variables
  • Combine Data: Merge data sources based on a unique identifier.


Feature Selection

Methods Used:

  • Correlation analysis identified relationships between features and over-demand, highlighting significant predictors while avoiding redundancy.
  • Feature importance scores from statistical models were used to rank features based on their predictive value.

Key Features Identified:

  • Leakage, Production Water Usage, Employee Count, and Daily Abstraction were the most impactful variables contributing to over-demand prediction.
